Cucumber Demo Project

Create Selenium Deamon/Windows Service

On OS X
Prerequisites:
Ruby
Selenium Server ruby gem

open Terminal.app and type the following:
    sudo mkdir -p /var/log/selenium/
    sudo chmod a+w /var/log/selenium/
    touch ~/Library/LaunchAgents/Ruby.Selenium.Server.Launcher.Deamon.plist
    open ~/Library/LaunchAgents/Ruby.Selenium.Server.Launcher.Deamon.plist
    paste in code
        :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
        <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
        <!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
        <plist version="1.0">
        <dict>
                <key>Label</key>
                <string>RubySeleniumServerLauncher</string>
                <key>OnDemand</key>
                <true/>
                <key>ProgramArguments</key>
                <array>
                   <string>/usr/bin/Selenium</string>
                </array>
                <key>ServiceDescription</key>
                <string>Selenium Server</string>
                <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
                <string>/var/log/selenium/selenium-error.log</string>
                <key>StandardOutPath</key>
                <string>/var/log/selenium/selenium-output.log</string>
        </dict>
        </plist>
        :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
Now go back to Terminal and type:

    launchctl load  ~/Library/LaunchAgents/Ruby.Selenium.Server.Launcher.Deamon.plist
    launchctl start RubySeleniumServerLauncher

The Selenium server should now be started and running on port 4444 by default.  You can check everythingâ€™s fine by typing:

    ps auxwww | grep -i Selenium

It logs to /var/log/selenium/.  You can check the error log here:

    tail /var/log/selenium/selenium-error.log



On Windows
Prerequisites:
jruby
Selenium Server ruby gem
Windows Resource Kit

open cmd.exe and type the following
    PATH\TO\WINDOWS\RESOURCE\KIT\INSTSRV.EXE RubySeleniumServerLauncher PATH\TO\WINDOWS\RESOURCE\KIT\SRVANY.EXE

create Selenium_Service.reg with notepad
paste in code
    :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
    Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00
    [HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\RubySeleniumServerLauncher\Parameters]
    "Application"="jruby selenium"
    "AppDirectory"="PATH/TO/JRUBY/INSTALLATION"
    :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Now go back to Terminal and type:
    sc start RubySeleniumServerLauncher